    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nThanks for all the hard work on the Py_LIMITED_API :heart: \r\n\r\nI tried compiling one of my projects with `3.0.1` and ran into a few issues:\r\n\r\nThe following produces an error when trying to compile with the Limited API enabled and cython `language=\"c++\"`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nb\"123\".decode(\"utf-8\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere is a full example: https://github.com/ap--/seabreeze-c-backend/tree/cython-limitedapi-errors/cython_pylimited_errors\r\n\r\nError message:\r\n\r\n```\r\nbuilding 'limitedtest.bytes_decode' extension\r\nx86_64-linux-gnu-gcc -Wsign-compare -DNDEBUG -g -fwrapv -O2 -Wall -g -fstack-protector-strong -Wformat -Werror=format-security -g -fwrapv -O2 -fPIC -DCYTHON_LIMITED_API=1 -DPy_LIMITED_API=0x030B0000 -I/tmp/build-env-f2q3qnhc/include -I/usr/include/python3.11 -c limitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp -o build/temp.linux-x86_64-cpython-311/limitedtest/bytes_decode.o\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp: In function ‘PyObject* __Pyx_PyCode_New(int, int, int, int, int, int, PyObject*, PyObject*, PyObject*, PyObject*, PyObject*, PyObject*, PyObject*, PyObject*, int, PyObject*)’:\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp:610:19: warning: unused variable ‘version_info’ [-Wunused-variable]\r\n  610 |         PyObject *version_info; // borrowed\r\n      |                   ^~~~~~~~~~~~\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp: In function ‘PyObject* __Pyx_decode_bytes(PyObject*, Py_ssize_t, Py_ssize_t, const char*, const char*, PyObject* (*)(const char*, Py_ssize_t, const char*))’:\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp:1562:9: error: ‘PyBytes_AS_STRING’ was not declared in this scope; did you mean ‘PyBytes_AsString’?\r\n 1562 |         PyBytes_AS_STRING(string), PyBytes_GET_SIZE(string),\r\n      |         ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n      |         PyBytes_AsString\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp:1562:36: error: ‘PyBytes_GET_SIZE’ was not declared in this scope; did you mean ‘PyBytes_Size’?\r\n 1562 |         PyBytes_AS_STRING(string), PyBytes_GET_SIZE(string),\r\n      |                                    ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n      |                                    PyBytes_Size\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp: In function ‘PyObject* __Pyx_PyUnicode_FromString(const char*)’:\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp:3728:65: error: ‘strlen’ was not declared in this scope\r\n 3728 |     return __Pyx_PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(c_str, (Py_ssize_t)strlen(c_str));\r\n      |                                                                 ^~~~~~\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp:1398:80: note: in definition of macro ‘__Pyx_PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize’\r\n 1398 | #define __Pyx_PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(c_str, size) PyUnicode_Decode(c_str, size, __PYX_DEFAULT_STRING_ENCODING, NULL)\r\n      |                                                                                ^~~~\r\nlimitedtest/bytes_decode.cpp:2698:1: note: ‘strlen’ is defined in header ‘<cstring>’; did you forget to ‘#include <cstring>’?\r\n 2697 | #include \"traceback.h\"\r\n  +++ |+#include <cstring>\r\n 2698 | #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030b00a6 && !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API\r\nerror: command '/usr/bin/x86_64-linux-gnu-gcc' failed with exit code 1\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\r\nx = b\"123\".decode(\"utf-8\")\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n_No response_\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.11\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.0.1\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
